author: Sihan Goi
text: Came here over lunchtime from 12 to 2pm on a Wednesday and it was not too crowded. This is a very powerlifting centric gym. There are only power bars - a range of Eleiko, Rogue and HS Power bars. The Rogue are in lbs. There are no hybrid bars nor weightlifting bars, but at least all the bars spin. I lifted with the Rogues - the centre knurlings are brutal. Equipment wise, there are 6 half racks and 2 full racks, 3 platforms, and at least 1 bar per rack/platform. Ziva bumpers (only 10kg, 20kg and a couple 5kg). There are also some old metal PL plates in the office. Loads of plate loaded and cable machines, cardio equipment, a large warmup area. Generally it's huge and open with no narrow corridors or areas, a good layout for a gym. Access is either via lift lobby to the right of Harvey Norman (when you're looking at it), or you can take the stairs/escalators from Harvey Norman to level 2 and exit to go to the gym. There is a shared unisex bathroom with a few female only stalls, sinks and Dyson hair dryers, but there are no toilets in the gym (there are public toilets outside the gym). Quite a nice gym that's well stocked in terms of equipment, but would've liked some WL/hybrid bars at least.

author: Jack
text: One of the better gyms in the east. Space is huge and well spaced apart. Plenty racks and free weights and most of the machines are precor, which is different from those I'm more familiar with using hammer strength. There is also a free to use body composition scale, where most other gyms will be only accessed by gym staff. Surprised though while changing room is spacious there is only one water dispenser which doesn't dispense cold water? Or maybe I don't know how to operate.

The gym itself is well-equipped, clean, and has a great environment that makes working out enjoyable. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced gym-goer, this place has everything you need.

What I appreciate most about Anytime Fitness Chai Chee is the convenience it offers. Being open 24/7, it allows me to fit in my workouts at any time that suits my schedule. This flexibility is a huge plus for anyone with a busy lifestyle.

Overall, Anytime Fitness Chai Chee is an excellent gym with great facilities, a clean and well-maintained environment, and a friendly atmosphere. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a reliable and convenient place to work out.

text:

The staff are also very sociable and accomodating, and are always willing to listen to the members' feedback with regards to any matter. Showering and changing facilities are also significantly more spacious than most other outlets, which adds to the overall comfort and feel of the place as well.

All in all, I cannot recommend Anytime Fitness Chai Chee enough. I have zero regrets on changing my home gym to this outlet, and I intend to stay with this outlet for the rest of time spent training.

I can say without hesitation, that this is the BEST gym I‚Äôve personally used here in Singapore! It is spacious, has new high-end equipment and its free weight and power lifting equipment is unmatched ANYWHERE.

They have enough space to make you feel comfortable; they have a huge array of equipment, machines and free weights. They have many different sorts of bars for free weight exercises. They have machines I have never seen in SG throughout my years of being a gym rat.

Staff are helpful and friendly as well which is a huge plus of course. All in all this gym definitely deserves a 5 upon 5 star rating. They have a few machines & cables out of order but I have spoken to the trainers who told me they have already requested for replacements/repairs. That would only increase their already superb gym. In any case the machines they already have which are in order are already more than enough & more than in any other gym I‚Äôve seen here in SG. For the time being this is my favorite AF gym here in SG! Will continue trying new branches out but I feel this would be a tough one to beat!

author: Hamid
text:
Lack of signage anywhere within the 4 blocks located there, may make it very hard for some to find it.

Location:
AFCC is located in the building next to Decathlon (on its left), where the Harvey Norman outlet is. Enter via the lift lobby, located at the front of the building. Take the lift to the 2nd floor. Upon exiting the lift, turn left and take a left again. Walk straight down, you'll see AFCC on your right.

Parking:
Parking at Viva B.P. is option 1,but cheaper option would be to turn into the HDB carpark further down the road, from the turn to enter Viva business park.

Layout:
spacious. Floor space quiet well utilized with good placement of equipment, machine and racks.

Equipment:
4 squat racks (if I counted correctly), and plenty of space to do compound movements like deadlift, clean and jerks etc.

Amenities:
this is where, to me honestly, they could have done better. A unisex locker room, is fine. But for a unisex toilet and shower area to be incorporated into the locker area, not such a good idea.
Total lack of privacy as the weight lifting area is right in front of the locker area.
Only 1 water cooler for such a massive gym, is quite a surprise for me personally.
Lack of shelf in the shower area is also quite distressing. No shower screen installed, so the shower area cum changing area will be very wet after someone showers.
Plus point is that there are sinks and mirrors along the wall, with hair dryers.

VERDICT:
All in all, a solid gym and kickass equipment with space (rare in SG).

author: Neo Kung
text:
Anytime Fitness is relatively large and spacious.
It‚Äôs the biggest one I think near Bedok.
But there are quite a lot of people there on weekends
Compared to community-based Anytime Fitness,
Fixed equipment is very abundant
However, I think the cleanliness of the toilets and environment could be improved.

The location is not easy to find. After walking in, you have to go to the second floor.
But the instructions were not very clear. It took me a while to find them for the first time.

The water dispenser is relatively advanced and is sensor-based, which is very good.
